Load data

df <- df %>% ungroup()

Model for each shrub species

CECO

dfCECO <- df %>% filter(Shrub_species == "CECO")
ggplot(dfCECO, aes(x = years_since_fire, y = Shrub_cover))+
  geom_point(aes(shape = df_source))+
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y ~ x + poly(x, 3))+
  theme_bw()
## Warning in predict.lm(model, newdata = new_data_frame(list(x = xseq)),
## se.fit = se, : prediction from a rank-deficient fit may be misleading

lmCECO <- lm(Shrub_cover ~ poly(years_since_fire, 2), data = dfCECO)
summary(lmCECO)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = Shrub_cover ~ poly(years_since_fire, 2), data = dfCECO)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -40.718 -24.312  -2.587  18.347  60.688 
## 
## Coefficients:
##                            Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept)                   39.87       2.30  17.338  < 2e-16 ***
## poly(years_since_fire, 2)1   114.38      27.50   4.159 5.54e-05 ***
## poly(years_since_fire, 2)2    38.34      27.50   1.394    0.165    
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 27.5 on 140 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.1208, Adjusted R-squared:  0.1083 
## F-statistic: 9.621 on 2 and 140 DF,  p-value: 0.0001216
dfCECO$pred <- predict(lmCECO)
gamCECO <- gam(Shrub_cover ~ s(years_since_fire, k = 4, bs = "cr"), data = dfCECO)
summary(gamCECO)
## 
## Family: gaussian 
## Link function: identity 
## 
## Formula:
## Shrub_cover ~ s(years_since_fire, k = 4, bs = "cr")
## 
## Parametric coefficients:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept)   39.874      2.296   17.36   <2e-16 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Approximate significance of smooth terms:
##                       edf Ref.df     F  p-value    
## s(years_since_fire) 1.659  2.048 9.119 0.000179 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## R-sq.(adj) =  0.111   Deviance explained = 12.1%
## GCV = 768.35  Scale est. = 754.06    n = 143
predCECO <- predict.gam(gamCECO, se =T, type = "response")

dfCECO <- dfCECO %>% 
  mutate(predGAM = predCECO$fit) %>% 
  mutate(predGAMseL = predGAM - predCECO$se.fit) %>% 
  mutate(predGAMseU = predGAM + predCECO$se.fit)
ggplot(dfCECO)+
  geom_point(aes(x = years_since_fire, y = Shrub_cover))+
  geom_point(aes(x = years_since_fire, y = predGAM), col = "purple")+
  geom_line(aes(x = years_since_fire, y = predGAMseL), col = "purple")+
  geom_line(aes(x = years_since_fire, y = predGAMseU), col = "purple")

Make fake data to make the plot lines smoother

x <- seq(0.5, max(dfCECO$years_since_fire), .5)
fake <- data.frame(years_since_fire = x)
preddf = predict.gam(gamCECO, newdata = fake, se =T)
fake <- fake %>% 
  mutate(pred = preddf$fit) %>% 
  mutate(predseL = pred - preddf$se.fit) %>% 
  mutate(predseU = pred + preddf$se.fit)

Pretty plot

ceco_plot <- ggplot()+
  geom_point(data = dfCECO, aes(x = years_since_fire, y = Shrub_cover), alpha = .3)+
  geom_line(data = fake, aes(x = years_since_fire, y = pred))+
  geom_ribbon(data = fake, aes(x = years_since_fire, ymin = predseL, ymax = predseU), fill = "royal blue",   alpha = .2)+
  theme_minimal()+
  ggtitle("CECO")
ceco_plot

OTHER

   filter(!Shrub_species %in% c("ARPA6_ARVI", "CECO", "CEIN"))

  geom_point(aes(shape = df_source))+

grid.arrange(ceco_plot, arpa_plot, cein_plot, OTHER_plot)

final_plot <- arrangeGrob(ceco_plot, arpa_plot, cein_plot, OTHER_plot, nrow = 2, ncol = 2)
ggsave("~/Shrubs-Seedlings/results/figures/Shrub_growth_time/gam_4_spp_COVER.png", final_plot, width = 10)
